General.EvolveInfo: Oree (#002) is a Digital Type Temtem.It evolves into Zaobian by a currently unknown method.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Oree is a small, android-like Temtem. It has blue, LED-like eyes and large black ear-like structures on the side of its head. It is black and light grey in color, and its body is disproportionately small compared to its head. Its hands are black and gauntlet-like with four grey fingers. It has two tiny black feet. It is mentioned in The creation of Digital Temtem 📚.One of the first prototypes created in Nanto Labs, Oree's early versions were the forerunners of Digital Temtem. Inquisitive creatures by design, they show great curiosity and a boundless appetite for information.

General.EvolveInfo: Zaobian (#003) is a Digital Type Temtem.It evolves from Oree by a currently unknown method.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Zaobian is a android-like Temtem. It has blue, almond shaped LED eyes on a black screen. Large black ear-like structures sit on either side of the head. It has four black plates jutting out of it's upper back surrounding a lighter grey patch. The lighter grey patch runs from the back to the chest on top of a larger black patch. There are a few other black patches on its body: two oval patches on it's knees, two triangle patches above the knee patches where the legs attach to the body, and four diamond patches on the upper arms, two on each arm. It's lower arms are bulky and gauntlet-like with seams going down the sides. There are four mechanical fingers at the end of the gauntlets where the hands would attach. It's feet are small and black.Zaobian are part of the second generation of Digital Temtem. Created with much more refined technology, they are more intelligent friends and companions, as well as sturdier in battle.

General.EvolveInfo: Platypet (#007) is a Water /Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves into Platox after 20 levels, which evolves into Platimous after 20 more levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Platypet is a platypus-like Temtem with a blue coloration, a white stomach and black platypus beak and tail. Its eyes are round, with black irises, white sclera and highlights. There are two black ovals near the far edges of its eyes. Two feathers point up from its forehead in the shape of a V. Six tufts of feathers sit on either side of its head closer to the neck, three tufts on each side with the middle tuft bigger than the outer tufts. Its arm and legs are short and stubby with three fingers and toes on its hands and feet respectively.Platypet was popularised by a cartoon series, and ever since then it has been one of the most popular Temtem with kids. The series had an educative purpose - to teach children that Toxic Temtem are also valid and can be good friends.

Locations.Route/Landmark: Xolot ReservoirInner large body of Acid
Xolot ReservoirOuter large body of Acid

General.EvolveInfo: Platox (#008) is a Water /Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves from Platypet after 20 levels and evolves into Platimous after 20 more levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Platox share common ancestors with Saipat, but the species diverged centuries ago - while Saipat developed opposable thumbs, Platox specialized in surviving polluted environments. Today they are the most successful feathered Temtem of Tucma.

General.EvolveInfo: Platimous (#009) is a Water /Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves from Platox after 20 levels and is the final evolution of Platypet.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Charles Temwin described them as "Platox, but more so". This is usually taken as classic Arburian understatement - Platimous were amongst the most successful apex predators before large scale taming, and remain very effective fighters.

General.EvolveInfo: Swali (#010) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves into Loali after 8 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Swali has a mint green body, in a brown cocoon-like coat that is decorated with a yellow ring pattern. It has a single yellow antenna on top of its head, as well as one leafy protrusion on its forehead which dangles as Swali moves. Its face has two large blue eyes with black irises and it has no visible mouth.When the harvest season is on, Omninesian fruit-pickers are always careful not to accidentally damage the delicate, chrysalis-like Swali. They grow on certain vines of the rainforest canopy, dropping to the jungle floor once mature and mobile.

Locations.Route/Landmark: Prasine CoastSecond large patch of Grass
Prasine CoastThird large patch of Grass
Thalassian CliffsGrass patch east before underpass
Thalassian CliffsGrass patch immediately east of the ramp valley

General.EvolveInfo: Loali (#011) is a Nature /Wind Type Temtem.It evolves from Swali after 8 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Loali has a mint green body with two small, triangular feet at the bottom. Its face has two large blue eyes with black irises, which are dazzling enough to hypnotise their foes; a straight horizontal mouth with two fangs; and two long, droopy, yellow antennae. One pair of wings connect to its body, which are sectioned into three, and are a deep greenish-blue in colour and decorated with green rings and yellow and green stripes. These wings are quite swift and allow Loali to change course in an instant.Delicate and graceful creatures, Loali are all wings and eyes - and natural charmers. Their hypnotic eyes can completely dazzle their enemies and their constantly fluttering wings allow them to change course in an instant.

General.EvolveInfo: Tateru (#012) is a Neutral Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: The base color of Tateru is white, and patches of light blue-green appear on the arms, legs and around the eyes; the only area of the body that contains no white is the ears. Tateru’s inner ears are navy blue, and it has short blue antennae drooping from the tips of its ears. The two eyes are black and beady, and the mouth is curved and not far below the eyes. Tateru has some dark blue oval shapes on the upper side of both legs. In addition, Tateru are stated to be amazingly tall.Despite their impressive height, Tateru are quite shy and not naturally aggressive. That's why they need proper training before battle. Wild Tateru are recognized for their upright position and sensitive antennae, always alert.

Paharo is a bird Temtem. It has red feathers, red gleaming eyes and a red diamond-shaped tuft above its orange beak. The rest of its face is covered by a leaf-like mask in two shades of green split by seven thin, dark green lines. It has a light circular patch on its underbelly and orange claws.Paharo tend to hide in treetops and lurk, their green "mask" allowing them to blend in with the foliage. Often the only way to locate them is to look for the telltale gleam of their eyes.

General.EvolveInfo: Paharac (#017) is a Wind Type Temtem.It evolves from Paharo after 7 levels and evolves into Granpah after 16 more levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Paharac is a bird Temtem that is predominantly red with a lighter star-shaped patch on its stomach, a green spiky mask on its face and big, red, sharp eyebrows. It has completely red eyes, an orange beak and orange claws. It has a fluffy, almost fur-like patch on top of its head.Due to their bigger size and stronger physique, Paharac doesn’t actually need camouflage, but they still love to flaunt their turquoise facial feathers with great pride.

General.EvolveInfo: Granpah (#018) is a Wind Type Temtem.It evolves from Paharac after 16 levels and is the final evolution of Paharo.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Granpah is a large bird with a leafy mask, seemingly split into two halves. It has light red plumage with a darker red collar and wingtips. It has long, yellow bird feet. Its yellow beak has four red feathers pointing out of it and a very light red, beard-like feather at the bottom. It has curved eyes with red pupils.The authoritative stare of a Granpah portrays the long time and many battles that it takes to achieve this evolutionary stage. They have earned their respect among younger Wind Temtem.

General.EvolveInfo: Ampling (#019) is a Electric Type Temtem.It evolves into Amphatyr by a currently unknown method.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Ampling is a small, black and yellow Temtem, clearly based on a deer fawn. It has striking, electric blue eyes, a tiny blue nose and yellow lightning motifs across its body. It has small yellow two-pronged antlers on its forehead and a small bushy tail.

General.EvolveInfo: Amphatyr (#020) is a Electric /Nature Type Temtem.It evolves from Ampling by a currently unknown method.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: The evolution of Ampling, Amphatyr inherits it's predecessors lightning motifs and electric blue eyes, however, it is significantly larger, and based on a full-grown deer. It has a tall, slender form and a pair of large, yellow, wedge-like horns. Its tail is flat and leaf-shaped, with a yellow lightning bolt of fur in the center.

General.EvolveInfo: Bunbun (#021) is a Earth /Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves into Mudrid after 20 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Bunbun is an orange rabbit-like Temtem. It has two long rabbit ears with cream-colored insides and reddish-brown tips. Its forehead, neck, and tail are covered in brown fur. Amidst the fur on its forehead, there is a green gem. Its upper face is orange, while its lower face is cream. It has reddish-brown eyebrows and green eyes, with a brown nose and two buck-teeth. Its body is white with a cream stomach. It has four orange legs. Its front legs have four green, crystalline nails and turn reddish-brown lower down, while its hind legs have feet entirely made out of green crystal.These adorable creatures are probably a remnant from the times Tucma and Kisiwa were a single island. While their strong Earth DNA is clearly of Kisiwan origin, the crystalline contents in their paws betray a definite Tucmani influence. They are social and easy to tame.

General.EvolveInfo: Mudrid (#022) is a Earth /Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves from Bunbun after 20 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Bigger and more resilient than Bunbun, Mudrid are hardy Temtem, used to extreme weather conditions. Their extremely fine sense of hearing makes them very valuable scouting Temtem once tamed... but also harder to catch in the wild.

General.EvolveInfo: Hidody (#023) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves into Taifu after 15 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Hidody is a caterpillar-like Temtem. It is predominantly mint green with a lighter coloured face. Its eight stubby legs, each with small suckers, have lighter green tips. It has big blue eyes with a black iris. It has a dark green leaflike collar.This cutie is an adept climber, thanks to the little suckers located in each of its eight stubby legs. For the same reason, Omninesian children quickly learn to hide their cookies instead of putting them on the higher shelf...

General.EvolveInfo: Taifu (#024) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves from Hidody after 15 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Taifu is a mint-green, quadruped Temtem. It has eight limbs; two pairs of arms and legs, respectively. Though it has a face, it has no visible head, and its body is a long, slightly bent oval shape. It has two thick, floaty antennae at the top. Its face consists of two round blue eyes and a mouth. It has an upside-down, darker green teardrop shape on its belly. From the top of its body extending down to the bottom is a dark green "cape".Brought up on a steady diet of stolen cookies, Hidody evolves into the more agile Taifu. They are naughty but cute creatures, naturally given to light-hearted mischief... but very serious opponents in battle.

General.EvolveInfo: Fomu (#025) is a Water Type Temtem.It evolves into Wiplump after 20 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Fomu has a blue, rounded body with four small, stubby legs. Underneath its belly extending onto its two back legs, it has a darker turquoise colour which is also present on the tips of its front feet. Fomu's entire backside is covered with a foam-like substance, and a singular strand of the foam sticks out from its forehead. Below the strand are the Temtem's eyes, which are shown to be closed, and in place of a nose, Fomu has an orange horn.These Temtem are known for their capacity to generate vapor, like charming little steam engines. Since that means losing a lot of moisture, this species prefers to remain in the water and use steam jets for propulsion rather than its short legs.

General.EvolveInfo: Wiplump (#026) is a Water /Wind Type Temtem.It evolves from Fomu after 20 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Wiplump is a blue colored Temtem resembling a unicorn, it has a pair of foamy wings and an orange horn. It has black shiny eyes with a turquoise underbelly. It is quadrupedal with four feet that have a black tip at the end of each oneWiplump takes Fomu's clever use of water vapor one step further - flying on steam wings, this species boasts increased range and speed, paired with a stronger attack thanks to its sturdier horn.

Locations.Route/Landmark: Mines of MictlanWater areas in route

General.EvolveInfo: Skail (#027) is a Neutral Type Temtem commonly found in routes on the island of Deniz. It is the first form of a two-stage evolution line, evolving into Skunch after gaining 17 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Skail is a weasel-looking Temtem with reddish brown fur. It walks on all four and has a big fluffy tail with a dark brown pattern on top. It has a dark brown mane and lighter colored fur on its stomach, around the mouth, eyebrows and inside ears. It has three dark brown diamond shapes on its forehead as well as two dark brown cigar-shaped hairs sticking out from the tips of its ears and four on the tips of its tail. Skail has purple eyes.This species of Temtem is notoriously bad-tempered, and tamers need all their skills to handle them. Once tamed, these muscular creatures can deliver powerful tail blows in battle.

General.EvolveInfo: Skunch is the final form of a two stage evolutionary line. It evolves from Skail after leveling up 17 times.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Skunch is a squirrel/weasel-like hybrid Temtem that gets around by walking on its hind legs and jumping around on its big fluffy tail. It has light brown fur with lighter parts on its hands, feet, stomach, bottom side of the tail, and around the eyes and mouth. It has long fur on its cheeks and forehead.There are darker coloured snipets of fur on the tips of its ears, ends of the fur on its head, spiky bands around the wrists, and a scarf-like shape around his neck. Its nose is also a darker brown. It has purple eyes with a dark stripe beneath them. Unlike their lesser brethren, Skunch are capable of bipedalism and can even stand on their muscular tails. This evolution allows them to pummel enemies with their massive fists... but it's done nothing to ameliorate their aggressive mood.

General.EvolveInfo: Houchic (#032) is a Mental Type Temtem.It evolves into Tental after 29 levels and further evolves into a currently unknown Temtem.It is one of the three starters along with Crystle and Smazee.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Houchic is a purple bipedal Temtem. It has white hair with purple tips and a rounded face. It has large, confident red eyes and a thin black mouth, with green dots on its cheeks and chin. Its legs and limbs are velvet purple. It has hands with four fingers and green palms. Its feet have two toes and green dots on each side of its ankles.Clever but somehow naive, the gentle Houchic are ideal as the first Mental Temtem for novice trainers. They are emphatic and intuitive, capable of understanding the subtleties of mentalism.

General.EvolveInfo: Tental (#033) is a Mental Type Temtem.It evolves from Houchic after 29 levels and it is currently unknown what it evolves into.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Houchic eventually evolves into the more mature Tental - shrewder creatures, whose writhing tentacles serve as apt metaphors for their ever-twisting, sibylline minds.

General.EvolveInfo: Orphyll (#035) is a Nature /Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves into Nidrasil after 22 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Probably a mutation from an ancient serpentine strand of Nature Temtem, Orphyll show remarkable adaptation to noxious conditions. They feature prominently in the art of ancient proto-Arburian cultures, who feared and revered them.

General.EvolveInfo: Nidrasil (#036) is a Nature /Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves from Orphyll after 22 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Long considered to be a legend, this species was scientifically verified just decades ago. Temtemologists are still debating how the nervous system of Nidrasil copes with three separate encephalic centers.

General.EvolveInfo: Banapi (#037) is a Fire Type Temtem.It evolves into Capyre after 17 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Banapi is a goat-like Temtem covered in soft, flame-like red fur. It has four legs with brown hooves and a brown "beard". Its tail is covered in the same fur as the rest of its body. It has a brown nose and two eyes which appear to be closed.Capricious and stubborn, these Temtem roam the side of the Anak volcano, grazing on burning coals instead of grass. Notably difficult to tame, they set the right expectations for prospective Fire Temtem tamers...

General.EvolveInfo: Capyre (#038) is a Fire Type Temtem.It evolves from Banapi after 17 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Capyre retains most of the flame-like fur it once had as Banapi, but it appears to have grown out of it. Its brown beard now appears to be a collar, and its eyes are now visible and are teal blue. Other than this, it carries all the other main features of Banapi.These temperamental creatures often appear in Myrislan folklore as tricksters, their unreliable nature embedded deeply in the culture. Highly territorial, they breed in Anak and make sure any visitors know just how unwelcome they are.

General.EvolveInfo: Lapinite (#039) is a Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves into Azuroc after 25 levels, which evolves into Zenoreth after 25 more levels or by trading it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Extremely common in Tucma, these little creatures are often the first Temtem of every young Quetzaleño. They are cheerful and resistant playmates for toddlers, and it is common practise to lightly file off the edges of their crystals to ensure safety.

General.EvolveInfo: Azuroc (#040) is a Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves from Lapinite after 25 levels and evolves into Zenoreth after 25 more levels or by trading it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: This Temtem is a common sight in the Mines of Quetzal, where miners appreciate their skill when dislodging big chunks of ore and gemstones. Its correct and expert handling is a professional requisite for most of them.

General.EvolveInfo: Zenoreth (#041) is a Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves from Azuroc after 25 levels or via trading. Zenoreth is the final stage in Lapinite's evolutionary line.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Any given night at the Jaguar Lounge, drunken miners whisper tall tales about great crystalline behemoths lurking in the darkest abyss under the city. This Temtem is probably the base of all those urban legends... probably.

General.EvolveInfo: Bigu (#044) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves into Babawa after 18 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Bigu is a mainly cream, slug-like Temtem. It has a mane of green leaves surrounding its head, and a blue stripe that stretches down to the forehead protruding from it. It has brown eyelids and blue eyes. Its pink lips are large and fat, with round white teeth and a red tongue inside its mouth. Its belly is a darker cream, with two sets of brownish open-circle patterns on each side. It has two stubby, cream arms. At the end of its body is a brown shell with dark brown markings.If there's an easily underestimated Temtem, that's Bigu. Comically ill-tempered, many tamers have found to their cost that these gastropods compensate their slow pace with outstanding tenacity in battle.

General.EvolveInfo: Babawa (#045) is a Nature /Water Type Temtem.It evolves from Bigu after 18 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Babawa is a slug-like, blue and white patterned Temtem. It has leaves running down its back and on its cheeks, and two white horns, two antennae, and dark blue stripe patterns below the leaves on its cheeks. Its eyes appear to be permanently closed or squinted. It has fat pink lips, with four round white teeth and a red tongue inside its mouth. On its lower lip is a brown spike. Down its body, it has six brownish, open-circle markings, in rows of two and on each side. It has blue, tentacle-like arms with white undersides and suckers on the bottom. It also has suckers on its lower body. Behind its tail, it has a brown shell with dark brown spiral markings and some green at the top. Its tail is blue with a white fin.These Temtem are flamboyant creatures with a funky sense of humor and boundless love for pranks and practical jokes. Many a naughty kid has donned a Babawa costume to cause havoc in the Quetzal Carnival.

General.EvolveInfo: Kaku (#048) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves into Saku after 11 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Kaku is a blue Temtem with a dark red flower - of four petals, each with two blue dots - on top of its head that resembles a rafflesia flower. It has a light blue round body and two stubby, triangular legs each with one yellow dot at the end. Its eyes are round and black.Less known than its evolution, Kaku are delightful creatures, cute beyond description. They tend to keep their petals wrapped around the body for protection, although no sane person would ever want to hurt a Kaku.

General.EvolveInfo: Saku (#049) is a Nature /Wind Type Temtem.It evolves from Kaku after 11 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Saku is small and round with grass coloured skin. It has black beady eyes and red dots on the corners of its ever-present grin. Saku has two stripes on its underside and a stem protruding from its back with four petals that resemble those of a rafflesia flower, which function as a propeller that lifts it in the air and serves as its primary form of travel. Saku also has four short, limb-like distensions that it can use to control its aerial movement, Its body contains inflatable air pockets.Some say the first airship designs were inspired by this Temtem's ability to inflate air pockets within its body, allowing it to float and drift with the prevailing winds.

General.EvolveInfo: Valash (#050) is a Neutral /Crystal Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: A fascinating offshoot, Valash is a rare case of bipedal hybrid, documented only recently. The care with which it keeps its forearm crystals sharpened betrays some sort of primitive sentience.

General.EvolveInfo: Barnshe (#053) is a Mental /Wind Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Barnshe is a bird Temtem that is predominantly fuchsia. It has a white stomach and a white head with a pink crown. The tips of its wings and its beak are pink as well. It has orange claws, very sharp, completely blue eyes, and two small dots for eyebrows.Traditionally associated with the University of Arbury as its heraldic Temtem, this species has a deep, piercing stare. Although winged, it prefers to keep to the ground and use its mind as a weapon - a symbolism the academics are very fond of.

General.EvolveInfo: Gyalis (#054) is a Crystal /Melee Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Gyalis have appeared in many horror movies. Sadly, this has resulted in a bad reputation as a "scary evil monster", not helped by its menacing appearance - but in the hands of a kind tamer, Gyalis can be every bit as tender and loving as the plushest of Pigepics.

General.EvolveInfo: Occlura (#055) is a Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves into Myx after 18 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Despite its creepy appearance, Occlura are mineral-eaters that never pose any danger to humans. Their tame nature and their appetite for raw rock make them valuable assets for mining purposes, as the Tucmani know very well.

General.EvolveInfo: Myx (#056) is a Crystal /Mental Type Temtem.It evolves from Occlura after 18 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: The oldest written records in Tucma indicate religious awe of Myx, considered to be embodiments of the "dark spirits". Some were considered to be celestial emissaries of Highabove, some evil messengers of Downbelow... but all were feared. With good reason.

General.EvolveInfo: Raiber is the first form of a three stage evolutionary line. It needs to level up 15 times before evolving into Raize, and 25 more times to evolve into Raican.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Raiber is a lion cub temtem. It is primarily red with stripes of yellow on its neck and rear side. It has scarlet pink eyes and has a shiny gold symbol in between. It has a small mane with ears sticking out the back of it.Raiber is often given to novice tamers in Omninesian Dojos because it is relatively mild-mannered for a Fire Temtem. Easier to handle than the mightier varieties, it is nevertheless a loyal companion and decent fighter.

General.EvolveInfo: Raize is the mid form of a three stage evolutionary line. It evolves from Raiber after leveling up 15 times and requires leveling up 25 more times before evolving into Raican.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Raize is a lion Temtem with predominantly red fur. It has a yellow three-part crescent moon pattern on its forehead, as well as yellow eyebrows and yellow parts around its ankles and under its chin as part of its big red mane. It has red eyes. Fierce and indomitable as the fire, Raize are difficult to tame but extremely valuable as fighting Temtem. Each has a characteristic birthmark on the snout, as unique as the movements of a single flame.

General.EvolveInfo: Raican (#059) is a Fire Type Temtem.It evolves from Raize after 25 levels and is the final evolution of Raiber.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Raican is the final evolution of Raiber, and evolves from Raize, as such, it is heavily inspired by lions. It has a thick, orange-red mane around a stern, intense, lion-like face. It has large, powerful paws, each ending in three short claws. Its ears poke free from its mane, and it has long fierce yellow eyebrows. Its snout and muzzle are thick, and its mane extends below the muzzle like a beard. Its mane is much thicker than that of its previous evolution, Raize, seemingly to imply increased authority and power.As the Tucmani legend goes, at the beginning of time, Tucma and Kisiwa were one single fire plain where huge herds of Raican ran wild and free, flame and Temtem being one until the Archipelago cooled and these noble creatures emigrated underground.

General.EvolveInfo: Pewki (#060) is a Water Type Temtem.It evolves into Piraniant after 13 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Pewki is a fish-like Temtem with a wide, flat, greenish-grey body. It has forward-facing eyes that are spaced far apart, and two small fangs jutting upwards, forming an underbite. It has a small triangular dorsal fin, much like a shark, pointing upwards from the centre of its body, as well as a large caudal fin with pink skin on the sides.Their flat shape allows Pewki to float right under the water surface, while they scout around using their huge, widely spaced eyes. Their iconic tall fins are often the only way to tell them apart from driftwood.

General.EvolveInfo: Piraniant (#061) is a Water Type Temtem.It evolves from Pewki after 13 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Piraniant has a grey underside with four fins, and purplish-blue starting from the tail fin and ending at the upper jaw. Its eyes stretch out into squares that end at the base of the upper jaw. The sclera is circular, with about a quarter of the bottom diagonally cut off. The pupil is black. Only the lower jaw is usually visible, which has seven large white teeth, the ones at the edges being bigger than the rest. The inside of the fins is a pastel red.A native species of Deniz, this Temtem tends to drift with the Sillaro current, so as to conserve energy... but once brought into battle, his size makes him a powerful fighter.

General.EvolveInfo: Saipat (#069) is a Water /Melee Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Saipat is a duck-like Temtem with a patient and strong demeanour. Its body is covered in purple feathers with red markings. Its face has a yellow bill and eyes with large black eyebrows. A dull navy blue clamshell helmet is fastened to its head with green seaweed. It wields a red coral sai.Nothing says 'amateur' like making fun of Saipat. Sure, they might look comical at first sight, but nobody who has faced a totally focused Saipat, sturdy coral sai in hand, takes them anything but seriously.

Locations.Route/Landmark: The Gifted BridgesSmall land area left-most of the route

General.EvolveInfo: Crystle (#072) is a Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves into Sherald after 30 levels and further evolves into a currently unknown Temtem.It is one of the three starters along with Houchic and Smazee.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Crystle resembles a green turtle with a green crystal shell. It has large orange eyes on the sides of its face, and two green horns on the back of its head. Its legs and mouth are a pale peach. It has two claws on each of its four legs, and green dots on its knees.Native to Tucma, Crystle are akin to smaragdine turtles, but they are actually closer to minerals than to fauna. Cute but tough, they are an excellent introductory Crystal Temtem for rookie tamers.

General.EvolveInfo: Sherald (#073) is a Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves from Crystle after 30 levels and it is currently unknown what it evolves into.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Sherald are known to evolve from Crystle- in the wild, as a result of exposure to the harsh environmental conditions of Tucma. They extract nutrients from the chemical interactions of metamorphic rocks and volcanic ashes.

General.EvolveInfo: Hocus (#079) is a Mental Type Temtem.It evolves to Pocus after gaining 21 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Hocus is a purple coloured Temtem with shiny pink eyes and a crescent-shaped object on its head, with a yellow blanket that covers its left eye. It has a floating pink ball on its head and a red stripe that stretches from his neck to the bottom of his body. It also appears to have no legs so it uses its powers as a Mental Temtem to float.Arcane and blue-blooded, Hocus have been selectively bred for generations and kept as dynastic heirlooms of the House of Braeside. They are fine weapons, trained to be battle Temtem for the ancient aristocracy, a rare sight nowadays.

General.EvolveInfo: Pocus (#080) is a Mental Type Temtem.It evolves from Hocus after 21 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Pocus was considered blue-blooded among the blue bloods, and was traditionally given only to the male heirs of the House of Braeside. When the lineage fell, they mostly went extinct... until recently.

General.EvolveInfo: Sparzy (#082) is a Electric Type Temtem.It evolves from an unknown Temtem and evolves into an unknown Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Sparzy is a short, humanoid Temtem with sea-green skin contrasted by dark-colored arms and legs, and a dark torso with a jagged cyan-colored "bolt" pattern. This dark coloring is also present in the form of a strip that circumnavigates its head and "masks" it's wide, yellow eyes in a manner similar to a raccoon. It has a wide, smirking mouth filled with large, blunt teeth and a pointed protrusion under its chin as well as a jagged thunderbolt-like fin on its head. It has large hands and arms which parallel it's short, stubby legs and flat foot pads, on the heels of which there are sharp spurs. Is very scary.Also known familiarly as "Sparky", this Temtem is a common sight in Cipanku. Children are warned to keep away from them - although normally good-natured and cheerful, they can involuntarily discharge considerable electric shocks.

General.EvolveInfo: Mushi (#084) is a Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves into Mushook after 20 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Mushi's distinguishing feature is the large, blue mushroom cap with white spots on its head. Its white body is within the cap. It has two drooping, rabbit-like ears and red eyes. There is a ruff of blue fur on its neck. Its body is covered in white fur, with two pink spots on the sides. Under its fur, there are two blue feet.Closely related to the non-sentient fungi of the Corrupted Badlands, Mushi are shy but territorial. Always mineral-hungry, wise tamers keep them well away from Crystal Temtem.

General.EvolveInfo: Mushook (#085) is a Toxic /Melee Type Temtem.It evolves from Mushi after 20 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Mushook are a hybrid variety, developed at the Quetzal Dojo by expert breeders. Strong and single-minded, some of the bigger specimens are occasionally employed by the Guards as static sentries at strategic points.

General.EvolveInfo: Magmis (#086) is a Fire Type Temtem.It evolves into Mastione after 16 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Magmis appears to have been inspired by sharks. It is primarily orange, with dark purple patterns. Its face is egg-shaped and has a crooked mouth and two large eyes that protrude out to the sides, which are almost entirely red except for the white sclera. From its chest stretching down to the beginning of the legs, it has a dark purple triangle pattern, stretching across its sides and two hourglass-shaped patterns on its back. It has two fins for arms; the flappy part being white. The top of the legs is a darker orange, returning to light for the rest. Its feet are rectangular and have two spherical toes. It also appears to have a dark purple horn or shark fin on the center of its back and top of its head.Magmis' original habitat was in the lava rivers under the Anak caldera, but now they can be found all around the Archipelago, as foundry operators in Quetzal, heating systems in Arbury... And, of course, in Temtem battles.

General.EvolveInfo: Mastione is the final form of a two stage evolutionary line. It evolves from Magmis after leveling up 16 times.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Mastione is a landshark looking Temtem. It is primarily orange, with dark purple patterns. It has a crooked mouth which is white at the bottom and in a hexagonal shape down the neck. It has two large sharp eyes that protrude out to the sides, which are almost entirely red except for the white sclera. From its chest stretching down to the beginning of the legs, Mastione has a dark purple triangle pattern, stretching across its sides and a dark purple pattern on its back continuing out to its big purple almost mermaid looking tail. It has fins on its arms and one on top of its head; the flappy part being white and purple respectively. The top of the legs and arms are a darker orange, returning to light for the rest. Its feet are like a dog paw and have two toes.Mastione are fire-loving Temtem, at home in the fiercest of blazes. They can be found grazing in woods devoured by wildfire. The tamed varieties learn to rein in their destructive tendencies - but even then, trainers should exercise care.

General.EvolveInfo: Umishi (#088) is a Water Type Temtem.It evolves into Ukama after 14 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Umishi resembles a sea slug. Its eyes are white with dark green irises and pupils and its mouth is triangular and light blue. Its head and upper tail are turquoise. Seven spikes protrude from its head; four short, thick ones at the sides, two long, thin ones near the top, and a single large, dark green spike on its forehead. Underneath the turquoise, Umishi is powder-blue and has wavy skin.The Umishi feature in many Denizan tales, usually saving drowning sailors and helping them get to shore. These so-called "sea-angels" are dependable friends, and the Riverine Fellowship recommends every member keep at least one in their squad

General.EvolveInfo: Ukama (#089) is a Water Type Temtem.It evolves from Umishi after 14 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Ukama, also known in Turquesa as "sea-sickles", are one of the fastest waterborne Temtem. They can easily outrun the sleekest sailboat, even swimming against the Sillaro current, so tamers have to use charm and guile to approach them.

General.EvolveInfo: Raignet (#091) is a upcoming Temtem and is rumored to be a Electric Type. It is known to evolve from an unnamed Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Raignet is primarily a bright yellow, heavy and metallic Temtem with a light blue arrow pattern down its stomach. Its head has two big grey horseshoe magnets attached to the back and sides, forming a helmet that it can presumably use to help move its body. It has what looks like grey armbands with blue spikes as well as flat grey feet with blue ankles. This makes it look like the Temtem is wearing armor. Raignet has sharp blue eyes and a black face. Interestingly, its upper body is proportionally bigger than its lower. When suddenly all the cutlery in your kitchen flies out of the window, you know this Temtem is nearby. In fact, it uses its magnetic power to move its own heavy, metallic body. The Cipanki always keep them away from their fridges.

General.EvolveInfo: Smazee (#092) is a Melee Type Temtem.It evolves into Baboong after 29 levels and further evolves into a currently unknown Temtem.It is one of the three starters along with Houchic and Crystle.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Smazee is a fluffy, orange monkey Temtem. It has orange fur covering the top, sides and back of its head, its back and its four legs. Underneath the fur is pale skin, which can be seen on its face, stomach and fingers. It also has patches of red, notably on its round ears and hands. It has brown closed eyes with red dots above them, a red nose and a thin, long smile.These little darlings have been bred for generations as playmates and babysitters for children - although capable fighters, Smazee are naturally cheerful and love playing and monkeying around.

General.EvolveInfo: Baboong (#093) is a Melee Type Temtem.It evolves from Smazee after leveling up 29 times and it is currently unknown what it evolves into.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Baboong are evolved, street-fighting Temtem, very popular in Lochburg, where they are often employed by pub bouncers. Although naturally good-tempered, they are as fierce as their hot-headed tamers.

General.EvolveInfo: Zizare (#095) is a Earth Type Temtem.It is currently unknown if it evolves into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Zizare is an earthworm Temtem who is light purple on the upper half/back and brown on the lower half. It has red eyes, a long brown chin, even longer dark purple horns and purple spikes on its back. One of the most remarkable inhabitants of the Kisiwan savanna, the powerful Zizare are the biggest creeping Temtem. Proud and territorial, they make for staunch friends.

General.EvolveInfo: Spriole (#102) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves into Deendre after 12 levels, which evolves into Cerneaf after 25 more levels.
Deendre (#103) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves from Spriole after 12 levels and it evolves into Cerneaf after 25 more levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: The young adult version of Spriole, Deendre are fascinating plant-animal hybrids that use their encephalic leaves to produce healing and nourishing components via photosynthesis.

General.EvolveInfo: Cerneaf (#104) is a Nature Type Temtem.It evolves from Deendre after 25 levels and is the final evolution of Spriole.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Cerneaf resembles a deer with large oak leaves by horns and the goat anatomy. Like goats, he likes to climb on high places, such as trees where he watches that his flock is not attacked. The elders of the towns respect this forest TemTem and wait patiently to change their antlers to use the leaves in different ancestral remedies to heal many conditions.Few Temtem are closer to flora than this species, a fascinating plant-animal hybrid that uses its encephalic leaves to produce healing and nourishing components via photosynthesis.

General.EvolveInfo: Toxolotl (#105) is a Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves into Noxolotl after 30 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Perhaps no other Temtem is as representative of Tucma as the colorful Toxolotl. Each strand in its mane is supposed to signify one of the original Tucmani tribes that first excavated and settled Quetzal after the Anak cataclysm.

General.EvolveInfo: Noxolotl (#106) is a Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves from Toxolotl after 30 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Noxolotl are noble, dignified creatures. They are taken to exemplify the resilience and spirit of the Tucmani people, as "a beauty born of the foulest depths of Xolot, a light in the abyss", in the words of the poetess Itzia.

General.EvolveInfo: Blooze (#107) is a Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves into Goolder after 25 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Blooze represent the opposite evolutionary path as compared to Toxolotl - blobby and bipedal, they are probably the oldest lifeform of Xolot, an atavic variety still largely unexplained by science.

General.EvolveInfo: Goolder (#108) is a Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves from Blooze after 25 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Not many agree to classify Goolder as an "evolution", for many of its traits seem to be vestigial features of a more complex organism, devolved to a more primitive or atrophied state. Its lack of legs is usually cited as an example... but its haphazard appearance conceals great strength.

General.EvolveInfo: Zephyruff (#109) is a  /Wind Type Temtem. It evolves into Volarend after 22 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Awkward fliers at best, Zephyruff rely on their speed and sharp claws to defend themselves. The sturdy, cloud-like tissue around the neck serves a double purpose, offering protection for the mother Temtem as well as a roosting point for Zephyruff chicks.

General.EvolveInfo: Volarend (#110) is a  /Wind Type Temtem.It evolves from Zephyruff after 22 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Volarend are impressive avians of great wingspan, strong enough to carry humans in flight. However, they are temperamental and picky mounts, and tamers are well-advised to treat them kindly, lest they are given a one-way ticket to the Downbelow...

General.EvolveInfo: Ganki is the first form of a two stage evolutionary line. It needs to level up 27 times before evolving into Gazuma.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Ganki is a large, flying Temtem. It is primarily yellow and black and bears many features found in both insects and bull cattle. It has gentle features and seems to be smiling and cheerful almost all of the time. It has two enormous, curved horns that end in a fine point, with a blue ring near the tip of each one. Its face is yellow, but features a small green circle on each cheek, almost like a small dimple. It has two small legs but doesn't appear to have arms, instead, it has four curved segments around its lower body, much like the wing segments of an insect.Many Cipanki legends mention the kind but powerful Ganki as mountain spirits, mythologically related to lightning and whirlwinds. Although they are no longer revered as kami, the Cipanki still appreciate and breed them.

General.EvolveInfo: Gazuma is the final form of a two stage evolutionary line. It evolves from Ganki after leveling up 27 times.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Gazuma is a large, flying Temtem. It is primarily yellow and black and bears many features found in both insects and bull cattle. It has gentle features and seems to be smiling and cheerful almost all of the time. On top of it's head is short brown messy hair along with a short brown mane. It has two enormous, curved horns that end in a fine point, with two blue rings near the tip of each one. Its face is yellow, but features a small green circle on each cheek, almost like small dimples and two ear like protiusions under it's horns. It has two small legs but doesn't appear to have arms, instead, it has four curved segments around its lower body, much like the wing segments of an insect. Just below the mane is four cloth like banners that seem to protect each wing.Even in the wild, younger Ganki seem to instinctively respect them as their elders. In the hills of Iwaba, one can often spot Gazuma leading small flocks of Ganki, a clear indication of their status among Electric Temtem.

General.EvolveInfo: Oceara (#115) is a Water Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Oceara is a quadrupedal Temtem. The top half of its head, back of the neck and back half of its body are colored pale violet, The bottom of its head, front of its neck as well as the front half of its body is colored dark pale violet. At the tip of its head is a small white horn while the back of its head holds four larger thin horns, two on the left and two on the right. The center of its body as well as its tail is covered in thick white fur, making it appear as though it is covered in foam.Very rarely seen in Deniz, Oceara are believed to be the basis for the legendary "serbatiyo" of the Sea-Queen legend. Their possession is a mark of distinction and prestige among Water Temtem experts.

General.EvolveInfo: Shuine (#122) is a  /Water Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Colorful Shuine are a sight to behold, their bright scales reflecting Pansunlight as they frolic in the Kakama Cenote. They feed off the acidic components of Xolotic water, acting as natural filters and keeping cenote waters clean and fit for human consumption almost as effectively as the layers of volcanic rock.

General.EvolveInfo: Nessla (#123) is a  /Electric Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Nessla is a large, aquatic Temtem that shares much of its appearance with eels. It has red eyes and its body is mostly light blue. Nearly all of the bottom half of its body is covered in yellow scales. It has several yellow fins located under its mouth, at the back of its head and near the end of its tail. The top half of its head is colored in light cyan and at the top of its head is an orange, triangular horn. The tip of its tail also has a similarly orange, triangular fin, while at the center of its body are two orange dorsal fins that are more rounded.Water and electricity are always a dangerous mix - and it's never as true as in the case of Nessla. These undulating, majestic creatures are at home in open waters, where their powerful electric discharges are most effective.

General.EvolveInfo: It is currently unknown if Valiar evolves from or into any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Valiar‘s distinctive characteristics are its long horn, thick white neck fur and loopy ears. Its face sports a distinctive purple and grey panda pattern, with the ends of the two grey ovals around the eyes carrying on to make a loop pattern around the ears. Its ears have the ability to expand and boost their mind power. At the start of the tail is more white fur, in the shape of a star. The tail seems to curve towards the body, forming another loop. Up to its knees, Valiar has purple legs. These break off and become dark grey, giving the legs a boot-like formation.Although nobody has managed to decipher their language, the Valiar are assumed to be extremely intelligent. The Arburian dons are still trying to come up with a scientific explanation for the way Valiar use their expanding ears to boost their minds.

General.EvolveInfo: Kalazu (#127) is a Water Type Temtem.It evolves into Kalabyss after 18 levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Kalazu is a small, squid-like Temtem. It is light coloured, nearly white, with dark blue speckles all over its body. Like certain squid, it has a cap on its head. Kalazu's cap has many dark blue thorns that surround it. It has eight nimble tentacles.Kalazu show remarkable fine motor skills with each of their tentacles. "Send Kalazu!" is a common expression of woe in Deniz. When you face a hard task, you might need a hand - when you need eight hands... well, you're in trouble.

General.EvolveInfo: Kalabyss (#128) is a  Water /Toxic Type Temtem.It evolves from Kalazu after 18 levels and is the final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Kalabyss is a large squid-like Temtem with large tentacles. It is light coloured, nearly white, with dark speckles of greenish-black all over its body. Like certain types of squid, it has a winged cap-like structure on the top of its head. This cap has a large horn off the front with smaller thorns around the cap similar to its pre-evolution Kalazu.How did Sillarian octopoda come in contact with mutagenic material is a matter of debate, but Kalabyss stand as an example of extreme adaption to the harshest environments - they have been known to survive a swim in Xolot Reservoir.

General.EvolveInfo: Adoroboros (#129) is a  Toxic /Mental Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Adoroboros is a primarily pink Temtem that appears to be made of a liquid or gas. It is hot pink with a pale pink underbelly, back stumps, lower jaw and oval on its forehead. It has two short, fat arms and two stubby legs. Its mouth has two pointy white teeth sticking out of its lower jaw, and its eyes appear to be permanently closed. Floating behind its back are a pair of dark purple wings. Its tail appears to be flexible, as it can wrap it around itself.Few Temtem are as deceptive as Adoroboros - an unusual mix of cute and deadly, combining the most sophisticated Mental tricks with the basest Toxic traits. They are a fine example of the incredible natural diversity of the Archipelago.

General.EvolveInfo: Tuwai (#130) is a Wind Type Temtem.It evolves into Tuvine by taking it to the Crystal Shrine. It's said to evolve into other Temtem but those are currently unknown.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Tuwai resembles a toucan, a species of bird. Its main color scheme is navy and green. A large tuft protrudes from the back of its head, and its eyes are round with a white sclera, light orange pupil and white highlights. It has a large toucan beak which is divided into pink and orange halves; the pink half is closer to the face. The head is navy near the top and green near the bottom. The green stretches out to cover its entire body, except for its stomach patch, which is cream-colored, and bird wings, which are navy with cream ends. Its tail has two feathers and is green with triangular navy tips. It has two small navy ellipses near the start of both of its legs. Its legs and feet are orange and bird-like, with two toes.Professor Konstantinos described Tuwai as “taxonomically Wind, but also the only Denizan Temtem with meta-mimetic properties.” He theorized about the possibility of Tuwai changing dramatically “if the relevant Place of Power” could be found.

General.EvolveInfo: Tuvine (#133) is a Wind /Crystal Type Temtem.It evolves from Tuwai after being brought to the Crystal Shrine and is currently the only known final evolution of it.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Tuvine, like its pre-evolution Tuwai, is based on a toucan. It has a green, crystalline body, and orange eyes. Its orange toucan beak has a green middle and tip, with a diamond-shaped light green marking on the front. Its head and beak also have dark green crystals growing from them. Below its neck, it has dark green wings with six lighter green feathers, also with diamond-shaped markings. Its feet are orange with dark green nails, and its tail has five diamond-marked green feathers.Just how a Crystal Temtem manages to fly effectively is still a mystery to most Temtemologists. Some theorize its flight is aided by magnetic repulsion generated by mineral organs... but most tamers just enjoy their emerald majesty without asking too many questions.

General.EvolveInfo: Kinu (#137) is a Nature /Mental Type Temtem.It does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: The elusive Kinu are some of the rarest Nature Temtem in the Myrisles - to the point that some tamers think they're a mere legend. When they do show up, Omninesians treat them with the respect reserved for the guardian spirits of the Banyan.Kinu does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

General.EvolveInfo: Vulvir is the first form of a three-stage evolutionary line. It needs to level up 14 times before evolving into Vulor, and then level up 28 more times before evolving into Vulcrane.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Vulvir is a dinosaur/dragon-looking Temtem with a rock covering its face. It is brownish orange in colour with lime-green eyes and red stripes on its abdomen.Some academics speculate that this is the last remnant of a long-lost "Draconic" variety of Temtem. In practice terms, most tamers classify them as Fire-Earth, which is an accurate designator for these mighty but shy creatures.

General.EvolveInfo: Vulor (#139) is a  /Earth Type Temtem.It evolves from Vulvir after 14 levels and evolves into Vulcrane after 28 more levels.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Although they hide their faces in hollow rocks like their lesser brethren, these Temtem have very little to fear from their environment. Tough as stone and destructive as fire, they are a force to be reckoned with.

General.EvolveInfo: Vulcrane is the final form of a three stage evolutionary line. It evolves from Vulor after leveling up 28 times which evolved from Vulvir after leveling up 14 times.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Vulcrane are sometimes described as "Anak on two legs". If a variety of draconic-looking Temtem ever existed, they couldn't have been much fiercer than this advanced, flaming beast.

General.EvolveInfo: Pigepic does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: Pigepic is a small, fluffy, pig-like Temtem. Its face sports small round eyes and a pink snout that resembles a heart. The front half of its body is adorned in a wine-red mane under which lies a brighter shade of pink skin. While large, Pigepic's short, hooved legs keep it standing low to the ground. Additionally, Pigepic has a curly spiral tail and a set of wings that it can utilize for low-speed flight. In its Luma form, Pigepic’s color scheme changes from dark pink and light pink to black and light blue.The absolute favourites of toddlers all around the Archipelago, Pigepic are fluffy, soft and absolutely adorable. Voluminous and cumbersome, they normally float low over the ground, making them ideal playmates for small children.

General.EvolveInfo: Anahir does not evolve into or from any other Temtem.

Appearance.AppearanceAndPersonality: This tortured creature is the result of Dr. Hamijo's attempts at creating a new "Diamond" variety. By picking the sturdiest variety of Crystal Temtem and submitting it to the harshest Fire environment of Anak, he has achieved something unique... and uniquely cruel.
